- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the gossip problem in distributed algorithms.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper discusses the expressive power of distributed automata, which is a topic in formal methods and logic.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes a non-deterministic gossip protocol for message-passing systems, which involves designing algorithms.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of finite local states and message alphabets in the gossip protocol, which is related to programming language design.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the expressive power of distributed automata, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory.
